
Requirements
============

- Python >= 2.2
- PyXML (included in Python2.3)

One-Step-Installation
=====================

As usual:

::

  # python setup.py install


There's a little EaseXML3-HowTo in docs/README. The HTML version of
this 'howto' sits in www/ directory. Some simple examples of how to
use EaseXML3 are stored in examples/ directory.

Feedback
========

Flames should go to djndnbvg@gmail.com
There exists a mailing-list where people can discuss about
EaseXML3. Send a mail to easexml3-subscribe@lists.example.com to
subscribe. Archives are located at
http://www.example.com/xmlobject-discuss/
